  "body": "**Only happens against the call-trace branch**\r\n\r\n### Discussion:\r\n\r\nMany of the `trace_` routines accept a `trace_type` (one of `trace`, `vmTrace`, or `stateDiff`). If one sends an invalid `trace_type` or an empty list of types to OE, it returns the correct `output` value, but no other data. TurboGeth defaults to returning `trace` data.\r\n\r\n### Difference:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5417918/101991312-d65c1380-3c79-11eb-957e-d895cc8d31bd.png)\r\n\r\n### Curl Command:\r\n\r\n```[bash]\r\ncurl -s --location --request POST --header 'Content-Type:  application/json' --data-raw '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\"method\": \"trace_call\",\"params\": [{\"to\": \"0xb9e7f8568e08d5659f5d29c4997173d84cdf2607\",\"data\": \"0x70a08231000000000000000000000000a25d04fa348f107428708ba19c95d1c79b3744bf\"},[\"invalid\"],\"0x3d0900\"],\"id\":  \"1\"}' http://localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Note:\r\n\r\nThis only applies to non-state changing `trace_call` invocations. If the `trace_call` would have modified state, a different issue appears as described here: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/issues/1406\r\n\r\n### Expected Result:\r\n\r\n```[json]\r\n{\r\n  \"id\": \"1\",\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"result\": {\r\n    \"output\": \"0x000000000000000000000000000000000000000000005c1d65b2473949e00000\",\r\n    \"stateDiff\": null,\r\n    \"trace\": [],\r\n    \"vmTrace\": null\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```",
